<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880309-0127 </DOCNO><HL> Ryder Begins Offer For 2 Issues of Notes </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RDR </CO><IN> BBK </IN><DATELINE> MIAMI  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ryder System Inc. said it began a tender offer for two issues of notes outstanding totaling $175 million principal amount.    The transportation and business services concern said the issues are $75 million of 14% notes, Series A, due June 15, 1994, and $100 million of 13.375% notes, Series B, due Sept. 1, 1994. Ryder said it will pay, for each $1,000 principal amount, $1,176.25 for the Series A and $1,167.50 for the Series B notes, as well as interest accrued to the date of payment.    The company said it expects the tender offer, scheduled to expire March 17, to reduce its average cost of debt.    Ryder also said it is considering a future purchase of all or part of its $100 million principal amount of 12.5% notes, Series D, due March 15, 1995. </TEXT></DOC>